2 SECTION 3, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3. (a) A law enforcement agency or law
4 enforcement officer may not request verification of the citizenship or
5 immigration status of an individual from federal immigration
6 authorities if the individual has contact with the law enforcement
7 agency or law enforcement officer only:
8 (1) as a witness to or victim of a crime; or
9 (2) for purposes of reporting a crime.
10 (b) A law enforcement officer may not request verification of
11 the citizenship or immigration status of an individual from federal
12 immigration authorities if the law enforcement officer, after
13 making a reasonable determination and considering the facts and
14 surrounding circumstances, reasonably believes that all of the
15 following apply:
16 (1) The law enforcement officer has contact with the
17 individual because the individual either:
